<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 03 at 4:04AM CDT  by NWS Hastings</headline>
<description>...Near-Critical Fire Weather Conditions Likely This Afternoon
With Briefly Critical Conditions Possible...
Although these counties are not currently under a Red Flag
Warning for this afternoon and early evening due to forecast
conditions falling just short of official Warning criteria,
solidly near-critical conditions are likely, with briefly
critical conditions possible. This will result from a combination
of northwest winds gusting as high as 20 to 30 MPH and relative
humidity dropping as low as around 20 percent, especially between
3 and 8 PM.
Despite the absence of a formal Warning at this time, caution is
certainly advised this afternoon and evening if engaging in any
activity that could spark a fire.</description>
